  {
    "section_type": "discussion",
    "type": "minutes_chunk",
    "document_type": "minutes",
    "document_subtype": "officer",
    "source_file": "February 23 _ Officer Meeting.txt",
    "role": "N/A",
    "person": "N/A",
    "content": "* ESS Volunteer Scholarship Opportunity\n* $3800 is too much\n* Could go through student life awards at UOSU\n* Graduate Photographer\n* Would be nice to have for professional grad headshots or as a back-up for W&C\n* Cyrus will reach out to contact\n* VP sustainability mandate ideas\n* Ryn bringing this up on behalf of squid, the following points are just paraphrasing what we talked about\n* No one is running for sustainability next year, sustainability is still important\n* They think the position could have more potential but not currently enough mandated to be a proper exec role\n* If its just consulting our practices maybe switch to commissioner, not that squid thinks thats the best option though\n* Expanding the VP Sustainability mandate could include other aspects such as economic and social sustainability as well as environmental\n* Squid is still passionate about the position but needs to exist differently than it is currently\n* Not necessarily a common position among RSGs\n* Are we planning to keep commissioner positions as strictly outlined next year as we are currently? Would there be the opportunity for sustainability to be more structured as a commissioner position in policy.",
    "meeting_date": "2026-02-23",
    "meeting_date_display": "February 23rd 2026"
  },
  {
    "section_type": "discussion",
    "type": "minutes_chunk",
    "document_type": "minutes",
    "document_subtype": "officer",
    "source_file": "February 23 _ Officer Meeting.txt",
    "role": "N/A",
    "person": "N/A",
    "content": "* Only faculty that does a fully catered dinner for W&C\n* Incredibly expensive to feed 500 grads who each bring 4 people.\n* Lowest price to feed all 2000 is $11/head\n* $15 000 for Fall, even more for winter\n* Dinner requires people to serve, makes a mess and is difficult to regulate\n* Could shift focus towards wine and cheese (literally)\n* Could shift focus to lighter fare, salad and sandwiches.",
    "meeting_date": "2026-02-23",
    "meeting_date_display": "February 23rd 2026"
  },
  {
    "section_type": "varia",
    "type": "minutes_chunk",
    "document_type": "minutes",
    "document_subtype": "officer",
    "source_file": "February 23 _ Officer Meeting.txt",
    "role": "N/A",
    "person": "N/A",
    "content": "* VP Social : Update on zeffy\n* New sales homepage that leads to all of our upcoming events (with tickets)\n* Cyrus’s really cool new reimbursement form tutorial\n* Replaces the F1 form\n* Can submissions get an email confirmation?\n* Note: Standing ovation was received\n* Nick double note: There was a sitting ovation\n* Commissioners Policy\n* Do we want to remove commissioners from policy and make them more ad-hoc positions\n* Keep them as appointment positions, but can put a post out if no one comes to mind for a position\n* Could select teams in the summer, or select team structure\n* Would be moving all commissioner mandates under their respective VP.\n* Mandates make it easier to see what you are getting into; for 1st-2nd year students just joining ESS.",
    "meeting_date": "2026-02-23",
    "meeting_date_display": "February 23rd 2026"
  },
